Masters in International Business (MIB) in USA: Best Universities, Eligibility, Admission, Courses, Scholarships, Jobs

  • 221 Reads
  • 3 min Read
  • By:CANAM Group
  • Updated On:Jun 29,2023 01:04 PM IST

Pursuing a Masters in International Business (MIB) in USA is a golden opportunity to gain experience and knowledge about the business world. Read the blog to know why to choose USA for MIB, the best universities, courses, admission requirements, specializations, scholarships, and more.

Welcome to the world of international business! Masters in International Business (MIB) in USA is a 1-2 years long postgraduate degree program offered in the world renowned universities of USA. It offers a unique blend of business strategies and international affairs, preparing students for a career in the international marketplace. Offering numerous options for advancing career in global market, international business is a popular course among international students.

If you are passionate about business and have the desire to explore the world, Masters in International Business is the degree for you! Read to know the highlights of the course.

Why Study Masters in International Business in USA?

  • The United States of America is home to some of the world's best universities for international business.
  • International Business course started first time in 1946 in American Institute of Foreign Trade, now known as the Thunderbird School of Management in USA.
  • Masters in International Business degrees in USA are accredited by The Association to Advance Collegiate Schools of Business (AACSB).
  • The demand for marketing managers is rapidly increasing, opening up 35,300 new job opportunities annually for professionals in this field.
  • Internship opportunities in International Business program in USA helps students to gain practical experience and inculcate skills.

Eligibility Criteria Masters in International Business in USA

Students must fulfil the following eligibility requirements to get admission to Masters in International Business in USA.

  • Bachelor's degree
  • Minimum GPA - 3.0 on a 4.0 scale (83-86%)
  • English proficiency test score
  • GRE or GMAT Scores
  • Relevant work experience of 3-5 years
  • Statement of Purpose (SOP)
  • Letters of Recommendation

Document Requirements
Mentioned below are the essential documents required to apply for Masters in International Business in USA.

  • Academic transcripts
  • Proof of English language proficiency test
  • GMAT or GRE test scores
  • Statement of Purpose (SOP)
  • Proof of work experience
  • CV / Resume
  • Letters of Recommendation
  • Valid passport

Masters in International Business in USA - Specializations and Syllabus

The Master in International Business program in USA offers various specializations. Here are the most in-demand specializations for MIB in USA.

  • International Marketing
  • International Finance
  • Global Supply Chain Management
  • International Human Resource Management
  • Global Entrepreneurship
  • Business Analytics
  • International Trade and Policy

The syllabus of the Masters in International Business program may vary by the university; however, it generally covers subjects like International Business Strategy, International Financial Management, Cross-cultural Management, International Marketing, International Economics, and Global Business Environment.

In addition to main subjects, students are often required to undertake internships or capstone projects. This gives students an opportunity to apply the theoretical knowledge gained in the class to real-world business scenarios.

Scholarships for Masters in International Business in USA

It can be expensive to study in USA, but numerous scholarships are available for international students pursuing a Master in International Business in USA. These scholarships can significantly reduce your financial burden, making your dream of studying in USA a reality.

Job Prospects
Graduates of the Master in International Business in USA can work in various sectors, including Finance, Marketing, Human Resources, and Supply Chain Management.

Job titles may include International Marketing Manager, Marketing Assistant, Global Business Development Manager, Human Resources Manager, International Trade Specialist and International Project Manager. The USA is a home to many multinational corporations, global financial institutions and international trade organizations that offer rewarding job opportunities to MIB graduates.

Masters in International Business in USA is popular among international students as it offers many benefits such as world-class education, ample job opportunities, and a multicultural learning environment. Whether you aspire to work for a multinational corporation, start your own business, or pursue a career in the consulting field, the Masters in International Business in USA will provide you with the skills and knowledge required to be successful in the international business world.

FAQ

What is the average cost of pursuing Masters in International Business from USA?
The cost of Masters in International Business in USA may vary depending on the university, but it generally ranges from $20,000 to $60,000 per year.
What is the duration of the Masters in International Business program in USA?
The Masters in International Business program in USA is 1 to 2 years long. It depends on the university and whether you are studying full-time or part-time.
Can students work while studying for my MIB in USA?
International students in USA can work up to 20 hours per week during the academic year and full-time during holidays.
What is the difference between an MBA and an MIB?
An MBA is a general business degree, while an MIB focuses specifically on international business. The Masters in International Business is for students who wish to work in the global business environment.
What is the salary of Masters in International Business graduates in USA?
Graduates of Masters in International Business in USA earn an average salary of 89,000 USD (74 lakhs INR).
